Regular expression metacharacters

1. . - Matches any single character.

2. ? - The preceding item is optional and will be matched, at most, once.

3. * - The preceding item will be matched zero or more times.

4. + - The preceding item will be matched one or more times.

5. {N} - The preceding item is matched exactly N times.

6. {N,} - The preceding item is matched N or more times.

7. {N,M} - The preceding item is matched at least N times, but not more than M times.

8. - - represents the range if it's not first or last in a list or the ending point of a range in a list.

9. ^ - Matches the empty string at the beginning of a line; also represents the characters not in the range
of a list.

10. $ - Matches the empty string at the end of a line.

11. \b - Matches the empty string at the edge of a word.

12. \B - Matches the empty string provided it's not at the edge of a word.

13. \< - Match the empty string at the beginning of word.

14. \> - Match the empty string at the end of word.
